.TH simple_shell 1 "16 Nov 2022" "0.1" "simple_shell man page"

.SH NAME
simple_shell \- A simple shell written in C for interacting with a Linux operating system.

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B simple_shell
[\fIoptions\fR] [\fIfile\fR]

.SH DESCRIPTION
A shell, short for "shell program," is a user interface for interacting with an operating system. It interprets and executes user-entered commands. In some systems, it's referred to as a command interpreter. A shell typically provides a command syntax for interacting with the OS.

.PP
.B Overview
The simple_shell is a command-line program that reads and interprets commands from a file or the terminal, then executes them. It serves as the interface for users to interact with the operating system. The simple_shell is versatile, supporting both interactive usage and the execution of shell scripts. Users can either enter commands directly into the running shell or place commands in a file for execution.

.SH RETURN VALUE
The simple_shell always returns 0 upon successful execution; any other value indicates failure.

.SH PATH
The simple_shell searches for executables in all directories listed in the PATH environment variable.

.SH OPTIONS
.B simple_shell
Options for the simple_shell command should be provided after the main command, separated by a space and a hyphen.

.SH EXAMPLE
To use an option with the simple_shell command, type the command followed by the option.
.PP
For example:
.PP
.B $ simple_shell -option

.SH BUGS
A single space is required after specifying an argument.

.SH AUTHORS
The simple_shell was developed by Godswill Kalu and Vatalis Ibeh.
